1. Melbourne City Discovery tour Historical images

16. Matthew Flinders

17. The remains of Captain Matthew Flinders, the English explorer who led the first circumnavigation of Australia, have been discovered ahead of construction works at Londonâ€™s Euston train station. Archaeologists identified him by an iron breast plate, which had been placed on his coffin before burial.

27. Elizabeth Street - formerly a creek bed

29. Severe floods often swept like tidal waves down the old creek bed which became Elizabeth Street. This photograph shows the scene after torrential rain in 1863 which flooded low lying parts of the city and suburbs, even Princes Bridge was under water and train services stopped for days.
